* Data acquisition script for {{ project_name }}
*
* This do-file implements the OPTIONAL `fetch` DVC stage — the only stage that
* writes data/raw/.
*
* To activate:
*   1. Uncomment the `fetch` stage block in dvc.yaml.
*   2. Implement the download logic in fetch_raw_data below.
*   3. Run: dvc repro fetch
*
* data/raw/ is treated as IMMUTABLE once populated. The rest of the pipeline
* (ingest -> validate) reads raw but never modifies it.
*
* NOTE: Run this script via `dvc repro fetch`, not directly. Direct execution
* bypasses DVC tracking and will not update dvc.lock.

* Import mint utilities (located in same code/ directory)
do _mintd_utils.do

* Download or copy raw data files into data/raw/.
capture program drop fetch_raw_data
program define fetch_raw_data
    * Add your data download logic here. Examples:
    *   copy "https://example.com/data.csv" "$RAW_DIR/data.csv", replace
    *   copy "/network/share/data.csv" "$RAW_DIR/data.csv", replace
    display as error "ERROR: fetch_raw_data not implemented."
    display as error "Add download logic to fetch.do before running: dvc repro fetch"
    exit 198
end

// Main fetch program
capture program drop main
program define main
    ParameterAwareLogger fetch
    log_message "Starting data fetch for {{ project_name }}..."
    capture mkdir "$DATA_DIR"
    capture mkdir "$RAW_DIR"
    fetch_raw_data
    log_message "Data fetch completed."
    close_logger
end

// Run if called directly
if "`c(mode)'" != "batch" {
    main
}
